<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="33" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,1531,1828]" pageId="14" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,281,1531,1557]" pageId="14" pageNumber="33">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The single row of transverse tubercles situated close to the outer edge of the corbicular area of hind tibia, and the large size (over 
<quantity box="[557,649,1570,1596]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.5" pageId="14" pageNumber="33" unit="mm" value="8.5">8.5 mm</quantity>
) separate this species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,1531,1828]" pageId="14" pageNumber="33">Light brown, apices of fore tibiae and marginal and discal tubercles of corbicle of hind tibia fuscous to black.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,1531,1828]" pageId="14" pageNumber="33">Head. Wider than long; tylus subparallel-sided, subequal to length of juga. Pronotum with posterior lobe with distinct, fine punctures. Scutellum with few, scattered, fine punctures. Hemelytra shining, with small, distinct puntures.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,1531,1828]" box="[197,1013,1802,1828]" pageId="14" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,352,1802,1828]" pageId="14" pageNumber="33">Old records.</emphasis>
